#: index.docbook:1054
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profile Data Part"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1055
#, no-c-format
msgid "Data from a profile data file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1059
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profile Experiment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1060
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Profile Experiment: A program run supervised by a profiling tool, "
#| "producing possibly multiple profile data files from parts and/or threads "
#| "of the run."
msgid ""
"A program run supervised by a profiling tool, producing possibly multiple "
"profile data files from parts or threads of the run."
msgstr ""
"Profileringseksperiment: En programkørsel overvåget af et "
"profileringsværktøj, der laver muligvis flere profildatafiler fra part og/"
"eller tråde i kørslen."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1065
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profile Project"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1066
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Profile Project: A configuration for profile experiments used for one "
#| "program which has to be profiled, perhaps in multiple versions. "
#| "Comparisons of profile data typically only makes sense between profile "
#| "data produced in experiments of one profile project."
msgid ""
"A configuration for profile experiments used for one program to profile, "
"perhaps in multiple versions. Comparisons of profile data typically only "
"makes sense between profile data produced in experiments of one profile "
"project."
msgstr ""
"Profilprojekt: En indstilling til profileringseksperimenter benyttet til ét "
"program der skal profileres, måske i flere versioner. Sammenligninger af "
"profildata giver typisk kun mening mellem profildata produceret i "
"eksperimenter af et profilprojekt."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1073
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Profiling</title>"
msgid "<glossterm>Profiling</glossterm>"
msgstr "<title>Profilering</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1074
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Profiling: The process of collecting statistical information about "
#| "runtime characteristics of program runs."
msgid ""
"The process of collecting statistical information about runtime "
"characteristics of program runs."
msgstr ""
"Profilering: Den proces hvormed der indsamles statistisk information om et "
"programs karakteristik ved kørselstid."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1079
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Event Types"
msgid "Real Event Type"
msgstr "Begivenhedstyper"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1080
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Real Event Type: A event type that can be measured by a tool. This needs "
#| "the existence of a sensor for the given event type."
msgid ""
"An event type that can be measured by a tool. This requires the existence of "
"a sensor for the given event type."
msgstr ""
"Reel begivenhedstype: En begivenhedstype der kan måles med et værktøj. Det "
"forudsætter eksistensen af en sensor til den givne begivenhedstype."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1085
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trace"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1086
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Trace: A sequence of timestamped events that occurred while tracing a "
#| "program run. Its size is typically linear to the execution time of the "
#| "program run."
msgid ""
"A sequence of timestamped events that occurred while tracing a program run. "
"Its size is typically linear with the execution time of the program run."
msgstr ""
"Spor: En sekvens af tidsstemplede begivenheder der sker under sporingen af "
"en programkørsel. Dens størrelse er normalt lineær i forhold "
"tilprogramkørslens udførselstid."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1092
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trace Part"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:1097
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tracing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1098
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Tracing: The process of supervising a program run and storing events "
#| "happening sorted by a timestap in a output file, the Trace."
msgid ""
"The process of supervising a program run and storing its events, sorted by a "
"timestamp, in an output file, the trace."
msgstr ""
"Spor: Processen i hvilken man overvåger en programkørsel og gemmer de "
"begivenheder der sker, sorteret ud fra et tidsstempel i en uddatafil, sporet."

